Modifications by clawd/scout (crypto-news -> crypto-news-lite):

1) Repository simplification for research runtime
- Removed large non-runtime surfaces (UI/site/mobile/widget/docs/localization/sdk/prompts and other app-facing artifacts).
- Reduced project to MCP runtime + research-relevant data/pipelines.

2) Runtime-focused structure retained
- Kept MCP server runtime under `mcp/`.
- Kept research data artifacts: `archive/`, `data/`, `.data/`.
- Kept selected research scripts: archive/rag/enrichment/indexing utilities.

3) Robustness improvements in MCP server
- Updated `mcp/index.js` fetch handling to gracefully manage:
  - non-200 HTTP responses,
  - non-JSON content types,
  - JSON parse failures,
  returning structured MCP errors instead of hard parse failures.

4) Operational cleanup
- Introduced crypto-news-lite naming and runtime-first posture for OpenClaw research workflows.
- Removed quarantined extraneous files/directories after verification.

5) Validation outcome
- MCP server remains functional with 48 tools available.
- Core news/trending/analysis/whale/funding tools verified callable.
- Some upstream-backed routes currently return 404 and are treated as degraded until endpoint mapping is fixed.
